<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL'S ANNUAL RAFFLE BANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A raffle held for the last 20 years that has raised $60,000 each year for a 
Catholic high school in Oxnard will be closed down under pressure from the 
district attorney's office, school officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Sister Anne Eugene Metcalf, principal of Santa Clara High School, said Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Gregory W. Bose's April 4 letter declaring the school's spring 
fiesta raffle to be an unlawful lottery will not be challenged by the private 
school "at this point." 
</P>
<P>
However, Metcalf said, school officials will push for a change in state law 
that she said "would allow drawings and other lottery-type events for 
charitable organizations." JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
