<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TORRANCE OKS ROSE FLOAT DESIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three giant raccoons frolicking on a log will be the featured characters on 
Torrance's 1991 Tournament of Roses Parade float entry, City Council members 
agreed Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Designed by C. E. Bent and Sons Inc., "Nature's Playground" had been 
recommended by the city's volunteer Rose Float Assn. as best representing next 
year's Pasadena parade theme of "Fun and Games." 
</P>
<P>
Bill Lofthouse, a representative of the float designing company, said the 
decoration of the mother raccoon and her two babies with pampas grass, wheat 
stalks and a variety of bark, leaves and petals will challenge the skills of 
Torrance volunteers. But Lofthouse said their experience from previous years 
should aid them in their task. 
</P>
</TEXT>
