<HEADLINE>
<P>
RED CARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The demise of the Red Cars back in the early 1960s was the beginning of our 
current transit woes; that was when mass transit began falling on hard times 
and the one-person auto began flooding the streets and highways. 
</P>
<P>
It's unfortunate that we've had to spend millions in taxpayer dollars on 
research that keeps bringing us back to square one -- a light-rail network 
retracing the routes of the old Red Cars. 
</P>
<P>
Because of our failure to act, the inflated cost of the rail system is far more 
now than it was in 1985. 
</P>
<P>
While the Los Angeles County Transportation Commission's recent action to 
approve a plan to build three new light-rail lines is welcome news, it is 
unfortunate that it has taken bureaucrats this long to act. 
</P>
<P>
Let's bring back the Red Cars. They worked. They got us to where we were going. 
And they were fun. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN FERRARO 
</P>
<P>
Councilman, 4th District 
</P>
</TEXT>
