<HEADLINE>
<P>
REPORTER MISSED POINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reporter Gabe Fuentes missed the point of the kickoff of the Southern 
California Gas Co.'s recycling program (March 27). 
</P>
<P>
Recycling is an old issue, already in practice in many places, that is now 
increasingly important. 
</P>
<P>
It is hoped that the gas company's involvement will encourage even more 
businesses and agencies to participate. 
</P>
<P>
Beyond that, this project is a double-edged sword. It's environmentally sound. 
And, by contributing the paper income to the Volunteer Center of San Fernando 
Valley, it will indirectly assist hundreds of nonprofit agencies in our 
community. 
</P>
<P>
If any other businesses are interested in beginning a white-paper recycling 
program, but don't know how to begin, my staff could advise. 
</P>
<P>
SANDY DOERSCHLAG 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 
</P>
<P>
Doerschlag is executive director of the Volunteer Center of San Fernando Valley 
</P>
<P>
