<P>
Infrasonics: The San Diego-based manufacturer of ventilators for hospital and 
home-care patients reported a third-quarter profit of $82,000 on sales of $2.1 
million, up from a loss of $72,500 on sales of $1.2 million for the same 
quarter the previous year. For the first nine months of the fiscal year, 
Infrasonics' profit stands at $246,900 on revenue of $4.9 million, contrasted 
with a loss of $236,100 on sales of $3.6 million over the same three quarters 
the previous year. President Jim Hitchin said the improved sales are due to the 
federal Food and Drug Administration's recent approval for the company to begin 
selling its high frequency infant respirator, a product that has boosted the 
company's market share. 
</P>
