MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No Art Conference in Cincinnati: Reacting to a controversy in Cincinnati over 
an exhibition of Robert Mapplethorpe's photographs, the College Art Assn. has 
discontinued discussions regarding the possibility of holding the CAA annual 
conference there in 1995. A letter to city leaders from CAA President Ruth 
Weisberg said that the "apparently officially sanctioned censorship" of the 
show and the indictment of Dennis Barrie, director of Cincinnati's Contemporary 
Art Museum, makes the city "an inappropriate milieu" because these actions are 
incompatible with the organization's advocacy of freedom of expression. GREG 
BRAXTON 
</P>
