<TEXT>
<P>
Rescheduling Woes: Long Beach Opera's "Pelleas et Melisande," originally 
planned for April 28-May 6, then rescheduled for April, 1991, because baritone 
Kurt Ollmann had a schedule conflict with another opera in Rome, has been hit 
with yet another schedule problem. 
</P>
<P>
Ollmann, who was announced to sing the role of Pelleas, now must cancel because 
the Rome production of "Ariadne" was moved to the same time in 1991. LBO 
general director Michael Milenski unsuccessfully tried to recruit two other 
baritones, including Malcolm Walker, who withdrew after he told Milenski he 
didn't want to do it in English. "It's the most incredible casting problem I've 
ever had," he said. GREG BRAXTON 
