<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH TO UNDERGO ROUTINE PHYSICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush, described as in excellent health, will undergo a routine annual 
physical examination today at Bethesda Naval Hospital, the White House 
announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Bush, who jogs regularly and plays tennis, continues to suffer from a mild case 
of arthritis in his hips, a slight hearing loss sustained during his flight 
days in World War II and allergies related to bee stings and seasonal changes. 
The exam will conducted under the direction of the White House physician, Dr. 
Burton Lee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
