<HEADLINE>
<P>
SINGLETON ARRESTED ON PETTY THEFT CHARGE IN FLORIDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From the Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAMPA, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lawrence Singleton, convicted of raping a 15-year-old California hitchhiker and 
hacking off her forearms, faced a Florida charge Wednesday of trying to steal a 
$10 disposable camera from a drugstore, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Singleton, 62, was arrested Sunday in suburban Tampa, but was released with a 
notice to appear in court May 2 on a misdemeanor charge of petty theft, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A security guard at a store in Brandon spotted him taking a $9.98 disposable 
camera, according to a sheriff's report. 
</P>
<P>
Singleton was convicted of raping runaway Mary Vincent, cutting off her 
forearms with an ax, then leaving her for dead in 1978. Singleton was freed in 
1987 after serving eight years and four months of a 14-year sentence. 
</P>
<P>
He attempted to settle in several California communities after his release, but 
public outrage over his release forced authorities to keep moving him for his 
own protection. He wound up in the Tampa area a year later. 
</P>
<P>
Singleton told deputies he lives at his sister's house in eastern Hillsborough 
County. A woman who answered the telephone there said Singleton stays 
alternately with his sister and his brother, who lives in northwest Tampa. The 
brother refused to comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
