BOAT COLLISION CAUSES OIL SPILL IN JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A cargo ship crashed into the side of an oil tanker in western Japan on 
Wednesday and caused a two-mile-long oil spill, a Maritime Safety Agency 
official said. 
</P>
<P>
The 499-ton freighter Sumiryu Maru smashed into the 121-ton No. 10 Waei Maru, 
which was refueling a ferry in Osaka Bay, the official said. The amount of oil 
leaked was not immediately available. 
