<P>
CARPET PULLS RUG OUT FROM LIBRARY PLANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reopening of the Garden Grove Regional Library, closed since December for 
refurbishing, has been delayed once again until early or mid-June because of 
another remodeling snafu. 
</P>
<P>
This time, it's a carpet that doesn't match. 
</P>
<P>
The library was closed Dec. 11 by the county for a periodic face lift and was 
supposed to reopen Feb. 13, said Gary C. Gray, chief of facilities and 
construction for the county's General Services Agency. Other complications 
delayed the reopening until March 26, but when a new carpet arrived in early 
March, portions of it did not match in color. 
</P>
<P>
"You'd have to be blind to not see it," Gray said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
