<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
WORK ON PIPELINE WILL BEGIN MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Work crews will begin installing pipe for the South County Pipeline project at 
Los Alisos Boulevard and Jeronimo Road on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Motorists are advised to take alternative routes to avoid delays while crews 
lay the 2,350-foot length of pipe. Pipeline installation will continue along 
Jeronimo Road until the pipe reaches Olympiad Road in November, project 
officials estimate. 
</P>
<P>
The work is the second phase of the Mission Viejo portion of the project, 
backed by a consortium of water districts and land developers. Eventually it 
will extend from El Toro to San Clemente, and officials expect to complete the 
pipeline by mid-1991. 
</P>
<P>
Once completed, the South County Pipeline will provide the area with a second 
major water pipeline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
