Photo, COLOR, Mark Langston, in his first start with Angels, pitched the first 
seven innings of a no-hitter against Seattle Wednesday at Anaheim Stadium. He 
came out after 98 pitches and Mike Witt pitched the last two innings. CHRISTINE 
WALTER / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, Langston Debut a (No-)Hit: The 
Angels' new $16-million man, pitcher Mark Langston, makes his Anaheim Stadium 
debut one for the books by combining with reliever Mike Witt on a no-hitter 
against the Seattle Mariners. Langston was taken out after the seventh inning 
of 1-0 win against his former team. CHRISTINE WALTER / Los Angeles Times; 
