<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041290-0120 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 203273 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 12, 1990, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 18; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
199 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HOELKER PACES RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore Mike Hoelker pitched a two-hitter and faced the minimum of 27 batters 
as Rancho Santiago College defeated San Diego Mesa, 2-0, in the first round of 
the Channel Coast tournament Wednesday at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
Hoelker, a right-hander, had eight strikeouts and walked none. 
</P>
<P>
He allowed an infield single in the third but picked off the runner. He gave up 
a single in the seventh but the runner was thrown out stealing. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago's first run came in the fourth on a bases-empty home run by 
sophomore Conrad Colby, his third of the season. Chris Floth had a sacrifice 
fly and Colby scored on a wild pitch in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago (25-5) plays Consumus River today at 2 p.m. in the second 
round. 
</P>
<P>
In the Alan Hancock tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 7, Hancock 3 -- Ron Brown (3-1) pitched nine innings, allowing five 
hits and struck out four for Cypress (18-14) in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
In the the College of the Desert softball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 10, Southwestern 0 (5 innings, mercy rule) -- Wendy Robinson had a 
grand slam and Kelly Newcombe followed with a home run for OCC (26-7). OCC won 
the second game, 1-0, over College of the Desert. Nancy Johnson had a 
run-scoring single. 
</P>
