By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CIRCLEVILLE, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A freight train plowed into a tractor-trailer carrying molasses, dumping 48,880 
pounds of the brown goo on the tracks Tuesday. None of the 21 cars in the 
Norfolk &amp; Western train derailed, and no one was injured, officials said. 
