<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE CLINCHES VOLLEYBALL PLAYOFF BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge men's team clinched its first Western Intercollegiate 
Volleyball Assn. playoff berth with a 15-10, 15-4, 15-12 win over Brigham Young 
on Wednesday night in Provo, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
The win ended a frustrating period for the Matadors, who had needed to win just 
one of their final six WIVA matches to secure the berth. 
</P>
<P>
But Northridge dropped four consecutive matches, including a straight-game loss 
to UC Santa Barbara a week ago, entering two season-ending matches against BYU. 
The Matadors conclude their regular season Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Behind Rafael Tulino's 17 kills and Mark Root's 16, the Matadors accomplished 
the mission. Coley Kyman also had 12 kills for Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
The win boosted Northridge to 12-10 overall, 7-8 in conference play, and 
clinched second place in the WIVA. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors with will meet the third-place team from the Harry Wilson Division 
in first-round playoff action April 25 at Northridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
