<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS: AT THE MOVIES; 
</P>
<P>
DOCUMENTARY LETS TOP SURFERS DO THE TALKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cowabunga, dude . . . "Surfers, the Movie" has arrived and will show at 7 and 9 
p.m. Sunday at the Ventura Theatre, 26 S. Chestnut St., Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Filmmaker and Ventura resident Bill Delaney has meshed surfing footage and 
interviews with some of the world's best surfers. The documentary does not 
include standard narration but instead lets commentary from the film's subjects 
explain the surfing culture. 
</P>
<P>
Currently on a swing through California, the film will be shown nationally and 
in Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are $5 in advance, $6 at the door. Advance tickets are available at the 
Ventura Surf Shop, 858 Front St., and at the Ventura Theatre. 
</P>
