<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
$40,000 TO EDUCATION FUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Max Salter said his appeal for supporters to contribute to the Beverly 
Hills Education Fund instead of his reelection campaign has raised more than 
$40,000. 
</P>
<P>
"The amazing thing is that a lot of of them were people I don't even know," 
said Salter, who pledged to match the donations with at least $50,000 of his 
own money. 
</P>
<P>
Although some of the contributors were unknown to him, most of the money came 
in after he made a series of telephone calls, Salter said. 
</P>
<P>
Salter and fellow City Council incumbent Robert K. Tanenbaum were re-elected in 
the April 3 election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
