<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ZONING REDUCTIONS TO BLOCK APARTMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles City Council last week unanimously approved zoning reductions 
to prevent apartment construction on portions of nine blocks in Atwater 
Village. 
</P>
<P>
In a single ordinance adopted Friday, the council changed the designation of 
the nine areas from medium to low-medium density. 
</P>
<P>
The new zone allows for the construction of single-family homes and duplexes. 
</P>
<P>
The areas include portions of the five blocks northwest of Fletcher Drive 
between Larga and Casitas avenues, the block southwest of Atwater Avenue 
between Silver Lake Boulevard and Garcia Street, and the four blocks northwest 
of Los Feliz Boulevard between Glenfeliz Boulevard and Boyce Avenue. Other 
portions in those blocks retain their present zoning for either commercial or 
single-family home construction. 
</P>
<P>
Renee Weitzer, planning deputy for Councilman John Ferraro, said the downzoning 
was initiated by residents to eliminate the possibility of apartment houses 
being built in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
