<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS NOTEBOOK; 
</P>
<P>
DINNER TO RAISE FOOTBALL FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach hopes to raise $100,000 for its football program at a 
"Long Beach Welcomes George Allen" fund-raiser May 23 at the Spruce Goose. 
</P>
<P>
Guests will include actor Walter Matthau, former jockey Willie Shoemaker and 
ex-football players Roman Gabriel, Deacon Jones and Billy Kilmer, all of whom 
played in the National Football League for Allen, who was named Long Beach 
coach last December. 
</P>
<P>
The dinner will feature sports memorabilia, artwork and trips to Europe and New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are $100 per person and tables can be bought for either $1,000 or 
$2,000. For reservations, call 985-4134. 
</P>
<P>
O'Bannon on TV: Artesia High School basketball star Ed O'Bannon will appear on 
the cable TV network ESPN at 9 a.m. Saturday in a tape of the recent Dapper Dan 
Classic in Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
O'Bannon scored 16 points in that game, which featured top high school seniors 
from throughout the nation. 
</P>
<P>
He will also play in the McDonald's All-American game, which will be televised 
on Channel 7 at noon Sunday from Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
49ers to Sign Hannibal: Roderick Hannibal of Poly High School in Long Beach was 
expected to sign Wednesday with Cal State Long Beach. A 6-foot-4 guard, 
Hannibal averaged 14 points and 7 rebounds a game this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
