<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: UNDERGROUND WORK TO CLOSE PART OF STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Department of Water and Power began work Tuesday on an 
underground construction project that will close the southbound lanes of 
Glendale Boulevard in Atwater Village for about 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
The road will be closed from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. daily at the Hyperion Bridge 
between Valleybrink Road and Riverside Drive. At other times, one lane will be 
open. Southbound motorists are advised to use Los Feliz Boulevard, Hyperion 
Avenue, Fletcher Drive or San Fernando Road. 
</P>
<P>
DWP crews will install underground ducts to ensure electrical service to 
residences and businesses in Atwater Village and Silver Lake. The project was 
made necessary by earth movement in the area, the DWP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
