<P>
NEARLY DROWNED GIRL, 5, CRITICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A-year-old girl who was found at the bottom of her grandparents' swimming pool 
in Fullerton remained in critical condition this morning at Childrens Hospital 
of Orange County in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Randi Newkirk and her 3-year-old sister, Robyn, were rescued about 1 p.m. 
Wednesday at 1831 N. Sunset Lane where their grandmother, Lois Newkirk, 59, was 
baby-sitting them. 
</P>
<P>
Newkirk pulled Robyn to safety when she saw that she was floating face down in 
the pool. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters called to the house later found Randi lying on the bottom of the 
deep end. By the time they brought her up, she was not breathing and her heart 
had stopped. Both girls were revived at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Robyn was listed in fair condition at St. Jude Hospital and Rehabilitation 
Center. A hospital spokesman said today that Randi, whose chance for survival 
has been rated as slim, was breathing with the help of a respirator. 
</P>
</TEXT>
