LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
2 TEENS ARRESTED IN ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people suspected of robbing a Yorba Linda bowling alley early this morning 
surrendered to police after a brief chase, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Grant Gulickson said two robbers armed with air pistols used a 
crowbar to pry open the back door of Village Bowl in the 18000 block of 
Imperial Highway at 3:15 a.m. They tied up a janitor and fled with with a 
pillowcase stuffed with an undisclosed amount of coins, Gulickson said. 
</P>
<P>
But the janitor freed himself and called police. An officer who responded to 
the scene saw the robbers' car leaving the bowling alley's parking lot. After a 
short chase, the officer found the car abandoned in the area of Oriente Drive 
and Lakeview Avenue in Yorba Linda. 
</P>
<P>
Gulickson said the robbers ran to a friend's house and telephoned their 
parents, who advised them to surrender to police. They were later taken into 
custody. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Michael Burton, 18, of Anaheim and a 17-year-old Brea youth. 
Burton is held on $10,000 bail while the juvenile, whose name is being withheld 
because of his age, was released to his parents after being booked on suspicion 
of armed robbery. 
</P>
<P>
Gulickson said officers recovered the pillow case of coins and two air pistols. 
</P>
</TEXT>
