<P>
DENVER, SEATTLE TO OPEN BOWL SERIES IN TOKYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Denver Broncos and Seattle Seahawks will kick off this year's American Bowl 
series at the Tokyo Dome on Aug. 5, National Football League commissioner Paul 
Tagliabue announced today. 
</P>
<P>
The game is one of four American Bowl exhibitions this summer, with others 
scheduled for London, Montreal and Berlin. 
</P>
<P>
Tagliabue said he hopes to expand the series, first played in London's Wembley 
Stadium in 1986, and is considering Moscow as a future site. 
</P>
<P>
He also said the league is considering scheduling a post-season game overseas 
for teams that make the playoffs but not the Super Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
In the other American Bowl games, the Pittsburgh Steelers and New England 
Patriots will play Aug. 9 in Montreal, the Kansas City Chiefs and Los Angeles 
Rams in Berlin's Olympic Stadium on Aug. 11 and the Los Angeles Raiders and New 
Orleans Saints in London on Aug. 5. 
</P>
